In the meantime the official agency Tass reports that the petition in question, in which it is declared that "the Italian people do not share the declaration of the President of the Italian Republic Sergio Mattarella and wish to apologize to the Russian Federation and the entire Russian people", has been signed by over 10,000 people. He told the Russian agency his promoter, the Italian journalist Vincenzo Lorusso, who lives in Lugansk and tells the life in Donbass. "The signatories are mainly Italian citizens, there are also Russians living in Italy," he said. Lorusso said that once the signatures were collected, the petition will be sent to the Russian Foreign Ministry to "demonstrate that Italians do not share the views of the president". &nbsp;&nbsp;
